# MVP Testing Checklist

Aim Brain must be testable from the start.

Every core feature should have tests before polish.

---

## Engine Tests

Test:

```text
PB calculation
latest score
last-5 average
last-10 average
all-time average
trend direction
consistency score
volatility score
weakness detection
neglected category detection
progress-only fallback
```

Required cases:
- one run
- no runs
- exactly 5 runs
- exactly 10 runs
- more than 10 runs
- improving trend
- declining trend
- inconsistent scores
- missing threshold data

---

## Scenario Matching Tests

Test:

```text
exact match
case-insensitive match
normalized punctuation match
alias match
platform-specific match
manual override match
ambiguous match
unknown scenario
```

Expected:
- ambiguous goes to review
- unknown goes to review/progress-only depending source
- manual override wins

---

## Benchmark Definition Tests

Test:

```text
valid definition passes
missing id fails
duplicate scenario IDs fail
duplicate rank IDs fail
threshold references missing scenario fails
threshold references missing rank fails
invalid universal category fails
missing thresholds warn but do not fail
source metadata stored
```

---

## Source Adapter Tests

MVP:

```text
built-in definition loads
local JSON imports
invalid local JSON fails clearly
```

MVP+:

```text
local CSV imports
CSV missing optional data warns
CSV missing required data fails
```

Later:

```text
GitHub raw JSON import
public Google Sheet CSV import
network failure handling
```

---

## Import Pipeline Tests

Test:

```text
import sample file
import same file twice
import malformed file
import file with unknown scenario
import file with missing timestamp
import file with duplicate rows
import crash/rollback simulation if possible
```

Expected:
- no duplicates on second import
- bad rows go to review
- batch report is correct
- raw payload is preserved
- transaction behavior is safe

---

## Database Tests

Test:

```text
migrations apply from empty DB
migrations are repeat-safe where applicable
foreign keys work
indexes exist
backup created before risky migration
```

---

## UI Model Tests

Test UI-neutral models:

```text
Home summary model
Import report model
Review queue item model
Benchmark source preview model
Settings benchmark definition list model
```

Do not test visual polish first.

Test that the UI model receives engine output instead of calculating it inside components.

---

## End-to-End Smoke Test Later

After MVP foundation:

```text
launch app
load sample data
see Home summary
open Import report
open Review Queue
resolve scenario match
see Home update
```

---

## Codex Rule

If Codex adds a core feature without tests, it must explain why.

Prefer small tested steps over big untested code drops.
